        <briefdescription>
<para>Detection probability for the power detector. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Pd = Q_1(sqrt(2·dwell·snr_power), sqrt(2·power_threshold))</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>snr_power</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Per-sample power SNR (signal power / noise power at the correlator output, linear). 0 gives Pd = Pfa. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dwell</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Coherent integration depth; must be &gt;= 1. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>power_threshold</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Threshold p, e.g. from <ref refid="detection__core_8h_1a657e4abcb2e394489fd46ae3093a630b" kindref="member">det_threshold_power()</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Detection probability in &amp;#91;0, 1&amp;#93;.</para>
</simplesect>
Example: det_pd_power(1.0, 4, det_threshold_power(1e-6)) ~ 0.78 (same result as det_pd(1.0, 4, det_threshold(1e-6)) since snr_power=1 corresponds to snr_amplitude=1 and the Q_1 arguments are identical) </para>
        </detaileddescription>
